 MBOMBELA –  According to the Department of Community Safety, Security and Liaison spokesman Joseph Mabuza, this follows a number of robbery incidences which took place in various health facilities over the past few months. The latest incident occurred last month in Mapulaneng Hospital where a doctor was nearly shot by suspects who were conducting a robbery at the doctor’s residence. READ MORE HERE: Mpumalanga’s state doctors fear for their lives On Monday MEC for health, Mr Gillion Mashego, MEC for finance, Eric Kholwane and MEC for community safety, security and liaison,  Pat Ngomane held a meeting where a security situational analysis was conducted on safety in all health facilities. Mabuza concluded that the meeting resolved that armed guards would be deployed with immediate effect to ensure the safety of the people, including patients, doctors and nurses.